  "response_text": "A close view begins on a pale aqua toilet with a glossy brown wooden seat and lid. The bathroom around it is warmly lit and homey, with teal walls, a wooden cabinet, flowers, and a doorway leading into a darker room. In the soft-focus background, a person in a light shirt walks away through the room, while the toilet remains in the foreground. After the person leaves, the brown lid begins to lift and fall on its hinges, opening partway, closing, then opening wider again, like a mouth moving on its own.\n\nThe setting widens to reveal a cozy, old-fashioned bathroom. A pedestal sink stands to the left, candles glow near the sink and on a side table, and a large window on the right looks out onto dense green foliage. The toilet sits near the center with a pink fluffy cover on the lid, placed on a small matching rug. The room is decorated with curtains, patterned wallpaper, baskets, and a dark pet bed near the window, creating a lived-in domestic space.\n\nThe scene changes to a sleek modern bathroom high above a city at night. Floor-to-ceiling windows show glowing office towers outside. Turquoise strip lighting outlines the glossy floor and walls, and a white, modern toilet sits to the right, glowing in the cool blue-green light.\n\nA grittier public restroom follows. The walls and stall dividers are covered in graffiti and stickers, lit by harsh fluorescent bars overhead with greenish and reddish tones. Two toilets sit in separate stalls divided by a central partition. Their red seats and lids lift and drop in alternating motions, again giving the fixtures a face-like, animated quality against the tagged walls.\n\nNext is a spacious, elegant bathroom with polished stone floors, black marble columns, tall windows, large potted plants, a bathtub on the left, and a white sink on the right. A white toilet is centered at the far wall beneath a framed picture, appearing almost staged in the middle of the luxurious room.\n\nOutside, in a foggy construction site, a blue-and-white portable toilet hangs in midair from crane cables. It is suspended between unfinished concrete buildings with exposed floors, scaffolding, railings, and tower cranes in the background. The portable toilet sways slightly in the open space, isolated against the grey construction environment.\n\nA tiled public washroom appears next, lined with seven white urinals mounted evenly across a pale green wall. Sunlight slants in from high windows, casting long shadows. Thin streams of water run from the urinals down toward the floor, making the row look active even though no people are present.\n\nThe view moves to a dim, warm bathroom beside a bedroom. A toilet with its lid raised sits near a sink, lit by amber light. Through an open doorway on the left, a bed with rumpled bedding is visible, suggesting a private nighttime home setting.\n\nThe focus shifts to a shower floor with reddish-brown tiles. Water and soap suds spread across the floor toward a square metal drain. A scrub brush lies off to the upper right. As the suds collect around the drain, the shiny metal drain cover resembles a small face, with curved openings like eyes and a mouth, surrounded by foam and bubbling water.\n\nBack in the graffiti-covered restroom, scraps of toilet paper suddenly fly through the air and scatter across the floor and stalls. The paper pieces drift and tumble in front of the toilets and fluorescent lights, filling the grimy restroom with chaotic motion.\n\nA close view then shows a light-skinned hand reaching toward a toilet’s small brass-colored flush handle. The hand wears several rings and emerges from the sleeve of a fuzzy blue garment. The fingers press the handle down.\n\nLarge white text appears centered over a blurred view looking down into a toilet bowl: “TAKE A LOOK AT YOUR PEE.” Behind the text, a woman’s face is visible out of focus as she looks downward toward the bowl. The rounded white edges of the toilet frame the image, making it feel like the viewer is looking from inside or just above the bowl.\n\nThe product appears in a bright, clean close-up. A hand tips a small Liquid I.V. packet over a tall glass of water, pouring white powder into it. The powder blooms and clouds as it dissolves in the water. The person holding it wears a fuzzy blue sweater. On-screen text reads “HYDRATE WITH” on the left and “LIQUID I.V.” with the brand mark on the right. The packet label also shows the Liquid I.V. name and identifies it as a hydration mix.\n\nThe final image returns to the construction site, seen from inside a partially built structure looking outward. The suspended blue-and-white portable toilet hangs far across the site among cranes, scaffolding, and unfinished buildings. The Liquid I.V. logo remains on the right side of the screen.",
